Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.description: Video file location in Cloud Storage.

params.name: data.segment
params.description: Video segment on which the annotation is run.

params.name: data.segment_label_annotations
params.description: Topical label annotations on video level or user-specified segment level. There is exactly one element for each unique label.

params.name: data.segment_presence_label_annotations
params.description: Presence label annotations on video level or user-specified segment level. There is exactly one element for each unique label. Compared to the existing topical segment_label_annotations, this field presents more fine-grained, segment-level labels detected in video content and is made available only when the client sets LabelDetectionConfig.model to "builtin/latest" in the request.

Compared to the existing topical shot_label_annotations, this field presents more fine-grained, shot-level labels detected in video content and is made available only when the client sets LabelDetectionConfig.model to "builtin/latest" in the request.

params.name: data.frame_label_annotations
params.description: Label annotations on frame level. There is exactly one element for each unique label.

params.description: Deprecated. Please use face_detection_annotations instead.

params.description: Face detection annotations.

params.description: Annotations for list of objects detected and tracked in video.

params.description: Annotations for list of logos detected, tracked and recognized in video.

params.description: If set, indicates an error. Note that for a single AnnotateVideoRequest some videos may succeed and some may fail.
